290
00:18:10,406 --> 00:18:12,346
Confidential inference protects the model.

291
00:18:12,726 --> 00:18:16,106
It does not protect the data
flowing to and from that model.

292
00:18:17,146 --> 00:18:19,745
The access layer must be
independently hardened.

293
00:18:20,546 --> 00:18:24,446
Take, takeaway number two:
CMCP is backwards compatible.

294
00:18:24,476 --> 00:18:26,946
You don't need to throw away
your existing MCP tooling.

295
00:18:28,766 --> 00:18:32,485
CMCP adds the attestation,
transform, and egress layers on

296
00:18:32,525 --> 00:18:33,716
top of what you already have.

297
00:18:34,376 --> 00:18:36,606
Adoption is incremental,
not revolutionary.

298
00:18:37,566 --> 00:18:40,926
And takeaway number three:
egress policy is a control plane.

299
00:18:41,766 --> 00:18:44,886
If you take one architectural idea
from this talk, let it be this.

300
00:18:45,576 --> 00:18:50,146
Enforceable cryptographically bound
egress policies are the primitive

301
00:18:50,206 --> 00:18:54,426
that makes AI data fl- flows
auditable and compliant at scale.

302
00:18:55,306 --> 00:18:58,626
Without them, we are relying
on model behavior and hope.

303
00:18:59,386 --> 00:19:02,406
With them, we have verifiable guarantees.

